[{"location":"api/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Functions","page":"API Reference","title":"Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Modules = [DitherPunk]","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#DitherPunk.balanced_centered_point_dithering-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"DitherPunk.balanced_centered_point_dithering","text":"Balanced centered point ordered dithering. Uses 6 times 6 threshold matrix BALANCED_CENTERED_POINT_MAT.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#DitherPunk.bayer_dithering-Tuple{AbstractMatrix{var\"#s4\"} where var\"#s4\"<:ColorTypes.Gray}","page":"API Reference","title":"DitherPunk.bayer_dithering","text":"Ordered dithering using the Bayer matrix as a threshold matrix. The Bayer matrix is of dimension 2^n+1 times 2^n+1, where n is the level, which defaults to 1.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#DitherPunk.bayer_matrix-Tuple{Int64}","page":"API Reference","title":"DitherPunk.bayer_matrix","text":"Contruct (un-normalized) Bayer matrices of level n through recursive definition.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#DitherPunk.central_white_point_dithering-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"DitherPunk.central_white_point_dithering","text":"Central white point ordered dithering. Uses 6 times 6 threshold matrix CENTRAL_WHITE_POINT_MAT.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#DitherPunk.clustered_dots_dithering-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"DitherPunk.clustered_dots_dithering","text":"Clustered dots ordered dithering. Uses 6 times 6 threshold matrix CLUSTERED_DOTS_MAT.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#DitherPunk.gradient_image-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"DitherPunk.gradient_image","text":"Create linear grayscale gradient image of type Gray.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#DitherPunk.linear2srgb-Tuple{ColorTypes.Gray}","page":"API Reference","title":"DitherPunk.linear2srgb","text":"Convert from linear to sRGB color space.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#DitherPunk.ordered_dithering-Tuple{AbstractMatrix{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:ColorTypes.Gray, AbstractMatrix{T} where T}","page":"API Reference","title":"DitherPunk.ordered_dithering","text":"ordered_dithering(img::AbstractMatrix{<:Gray}, mat::AbstractMatrix; invert_map=false)::BitMatrix\n\nOrdered dithering using threshold maps. Takes a grayscale image img and a normalized threshold matrix mat. The threshold matrix is repeatedly tiled to match the size of img and is then applied as a per-pixel threshold map. Optionally, this final threshold map can be inverted by selecting invert_map=true.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#DitherPunk.print_braille-Tuple{BitMatrix}","page":"API Reference","title":"DitherPunk.print_braille","text":"(Ab)use spy to interpret image as sparse array and print \"sparsity pattern\" in braille through UnicodePlots.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#DitherPunk.rhombus_dithering-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"DitherPunk.rhombus_dithering","text":"Diagonal ordered matrix with balanced centered points, ordered dithering. Uses 8 times 8 threshold matrix.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#DitherPunk.show_dither-Tuple{BitMatrix}","page":"API Reference","title":"DitherPunk.show_dither","text":"Apply Gray to indicate that image should be interpreted as a grayscale image. Optionally upscale image by integer value.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#DitherPunk.srgb2linear-Tuple{ColorTypes.Gray}","page":"API Reference","title":"DitherPunk.srgb2linear","text":"Convert from sRGB to linear color space.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#DitherPunk.test_on_gradient-Tuple{Function}","page":"API Reference","title":"DitherPunk.test_on_gradient","text":"Test dithering algorithm alg on linear grayscale gradient from gradient_image and show stacked plot.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#DitherPunk.tile_matrix-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"DitherPunk.tile_matrix","text":"Repeatedly tile a smaller matrix mat to fill out an image of height h and width w.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#DitherPunk.upscale-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"DitherPunk.upscale","text":"Upscale image by repeating individual pixels.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/","page":"Get started","title":"Get started","text":"EditURL = \"https://github.com/adrhill/DitherPunk.jl/blob/master/docs/literate/simple_example.jl\"","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/#Example","page":"Get started","title":"Example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/#Preprocessing","page":"Get started","title":"Preprocessing","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/","page":"Get started","title":"Get started","text":"We start out by loading an image, in this case the lighthouse from TestImages.jl.","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/","page":"Get started","title":"Get started","text":"using DitherPunk\nusing Images\nusing ImageTransformations\nusing ImageContrastAdjustment\nusing TestImages\n\nimg = testimage(\"lighthouse\")","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/","page":"Get started","title":"Get started","text":"Normalizing the image can emphasize the effect of the algorithms. It is highly recommended to play around with algorithms such as those provided by ImageContrastAdjustment.jl","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/","page":"Get started","title":"Get started","text":"img = Gray.(img) # covert to grayscale\nimg = adjust_histogram(img, LinearStretching()) # normalize","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/#Dithering","page":"Get started","title":"Dithering","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/","page":"Get started","title":"Get started","text":"We can now apply dithering algorithms of our choice, for example balanced_centered_point_dithering.","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/","page":"Get started","title":"Get started","text":"dither = balanced_centered_point_dithering(img);\nnothing #hide","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/#Visualizing-the-result","page":"Get started","title":"Visualizing the result","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/","page":"Get started","title":"Get started","text":"The dithering algorithms return binary matrices of type BitMatrix. These can be shown by casting them to grayscale using Gray.().","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/","page":"Get started","title":"Get started","text":"Gray.(dither)","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/#Working-with-small-images","page":"Get started","title":"Working with small images","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/","page":"Get started","title":"Get started","text":"The previous balanced_centered_point_dithering algorithm has a large characteristic pattern. Some algorithms work better on smaller images, for example bayer_dithering, another ordered dithering algorithm that leads to characteristic cross-hatch patterns.","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/","page":"Get started","title":"Get started","text":"img = imresize(img; ratio=1 / 5) # downscale\ndither = bayer_dithering(img);\nnothing #hide","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/","page":"Get started","title":"Get started","text":"The function show_dither casts to Gray and provides an additional integer scaling parameter to print \"chunkier\" pixels.","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/","page":"Get started","title":"Get started","text":"show_dither(dither; scale=3)","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/","page":"Get started","title":"Get started","text":"Alternatively, the images can also be printed to console though UnicodePlots by using print_braille","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/","page":"Get started","title":"Get started","text":"print_braille(dither)","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/","page":"Get started","title":"Get started","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/simple_example/","page":"Get started","title":"Get started","text":"This page was generated using Literate.jl.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = DitherPunk","category":"page"},{"location":"#DitherPunk.jl","page":"Home","title":"DitherPunk.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for DitherPunk.jl. A dithering / digital halftoning package inspired by Lucas Pope's Obra Dinn and Surma.","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/gallery/","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"EditURL = \"https://github.com/adrhill/DitherPunk.jl/blob/master/docs/literate/gallery.jl\"","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/gallery/","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"using DitherPunk\nusing Images","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/gallery/#Gallery","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"generated/gallery/#On-sRGB-and-linear-colorspaces","page":"Gallery","title":"On sRGB and linear colorspaces","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"generated/gallery/","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"A simple linear gradient works well to reveal the characteristic patterns of different dithering algorithms.","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/gallery/","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"srbg, linear = gradient_image(100, 800);\nmosaicview(srbg, linear)","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/gallery/","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"The pixel intensities in the image srgb increase linearly from 0 to 1. The second image linear has been converted from sRGB to a linear representation, which more closely matches our human perception of brightness.","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/gallery/","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"The helper function test_on_gradient takes a dithering algorithm and runs it on both the srgb and the linear image. It then shows a comparison of both inputs and outputs.","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/gallery/","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"Most dithering algorithms in DitherPunk.jl provide an optional parameter to_linear, which converts the input image to a linear colorspace before applying the dithering. Select what looks best!","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/gallery/#Threshold-dithering","page":"Gallery","title":"Threshold dithering","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"generated/gallery/#threshold_dithering","page":"Gallery","title":"threshold_dithering","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"generated/gallery/","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"test_on_gradient(threshold_dithering)","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/gallery/#white_noise_dithering","page":"Gallery","title":"white_noise_dithering","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"generated/gallery/","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"test_on_gradient(white_noise_dithering)","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/gallery/#Ordered-dithering-on-small-images","page":"Gallery","title":"Ordered dithering on small images","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"generated/gallery/#bayer_dithering","page":"Gallery","title":"bayer_dithering","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"generated/gallery/","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"test_on_gradient(bayer_dithering)","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/gallery/","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"The order of the Bayer-matrix can be specified through the parameter level, which defaults to 1.","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/gallery/","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"bayer_dithering_algs = [(img) -> (bayer_dithering(img; level=level)) for level in 4:-1:0]\ntest_on_gradient(bayer_dithering_algs)","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/gallery/#Ordered-dithering-on-large-images","page":"Gallery","title":"Ordered dithering on large images","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"generated/gallery/","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"The following methods have large characteristic patterns and are therefore better suited for large images.","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/gallery/#clustered_dots_dithering","page":"Gallery","title":"clustered_dots_dithering","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"generated/gallery/","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"test_on_gradient(clustered_dots_dithering)","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/gallery/#balanced_centered_point_dithering","page":"Gallery","title":"balanced_centered_point_dithering","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"generated/gallery/","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"test_on_gradient(balanced_centered_point_dithering)","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/gallery/#rhombus_dithering","page":"Gallery","title":"rhombus_dithering","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"generated/gallery/","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"test_on_gradient(rhombus_dithering)","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/gallery/","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"generated/gallery/","page":"Gallery","title":"Gallery","text":"This page was generated using Literate.jl.","category":"page"}]
